parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cooling fan can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine, loss of power, and potentially a fire, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: smoke or flames come from the engine compartment
the cooling fan does not turn on
or the fan makes a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause electrical system failures, leading to loss of power, engine stalling, and potentially a fire, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: the vehicle's accessories do not function

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause engine damage, leading to loss of power, overheating, and potentially a fire, which can result in accidents or injuries.
The failure of the wiring harness can cause electrical shorts, leading to fires, stalling, and loss of vehicle control, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: smoke or fire from under the hood
failure of electrical systems such as ABS

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause loss of vehicle control, stalling, and electrical fires, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Failure of electrical systems such as ABS
smoke or fire from under the hood
dimming or failure of interior lights and brake lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
transmission fails to engage into gear
speedometer needle flips over to zero
transmission jumps from overdrive to third gear

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Gear shift problems can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Gear shift gets stuck in park or reverse
gear shift lever and knob fail
gear shift slips out of gear
vehicle rolls when gear shift is not fully engaged
key can be removed from ignition without gear fully engaged into park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical issues can cause the vehicle to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: throttle sticks at wide open position
